 The IPv4 header contains routing and control information required to deliver packets from source to destination.
      
IPv4 Header Fields :

Version – IP version (IPv4 = 4)
IHL (Internet Header Length) – Header size
Type of Service (ToS / DSCP) – Packet priority & QoS
Total Length – Header + data size
Identification – Packet ID for fragmentation
Flags – Fragment control (DF, MF)
Fragment Offset – Fragment position
TTL (Time To Live) – Packet lifetime
Protocol – Next-layer protocol (TCP=6, UDP=17, ICMP=1)
Header Checksum – Error checking
Source IP Address – Sender IP
Destination IP Address – Receiver IP
Options (Optional) – Extra features
Padding – Align header to 32 bits
